==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amanita
<hw>Am`a*ni"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Amanitine</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of poisonous
fungi of the family <fam>Agaricace⟦ae⟧</fam>, characterized by having a
volva, an annulus, and white spores. The species resemble edible
mushrooms, and are frequently mistaken for them. <spn>Amanita
muscaria</spn>, syn. <spn>Agaricus muscarius</spn>, is the fly amanita,
or fly agaric; and <spn>Agaricus phalloides</spn> is the death cup (or
death cap).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amanitine</ent>⟦br⟧
